<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbc12e900-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s2279"><num value="2279">§ 2279.</num><heading> Applicability of other laws</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Sections 2274 to 2278b of this title shall not exclude the applicable provisions of any other laws.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbc12e901-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1946-08-01/ch724">Aug. 1, 1946, ch. 724</ref>, title I, § 231, formerly § 229, as added <ref href="/us/act/1954-08-30/ch1073/s1">Aug. 30, 1954, ch. 1073, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68/959">68 Stat. 959</ref>; renumbered § 231 and amended <ref href="/us/act/1956-08-06/ch1015">Aug. 6, 1956, ch. 1015</ref>, §§ 6, 7, <ref href="/us/stat/70/1070">70 Stat. 1070</ref>; renumbered title I, <ref href="/us/pl/102/486/tIX/s902/a/8">Pub. L. 102–486, title IX, § 902(a)(8)</ref>, <date date="1992-10-24">Oct. 24, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/2944">106 Stat. 2944</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
